definition: (of a mountain) high and tapered peak or summit/mountain-like in appearance/highest level/classifier for camels
a period of time/phase/stage/classifier for issues of a periodical, courses of study/time/term/period/to hope/Taiwan pr. [qi2]

sentences.english: However, over the next few years is the expansion of our para-xylene peak.
sentences.chinese: 不过，未来几年也是我国对二甲苯扩能的高峰期。

sentences.english: Winter is usually the peak season for norovirus outbreaks in Japan .
sentences.chinese: 冬季通常是日本爆发诺沃克病毒感染的高峰期。

sentences.english: A 25 minute journey can easily become a 90 minute journey during rush hour.
sentences.chinese: 在高峰期一趟25分钟的路程很容易变成90分钟的。

sentences.english: Place your call at a non-peak time.
sentences.chinese: 在非高峰期时打电话预订。

sentences.english: In 1962, at the height of the Cold War.
sentences.chinese: 在一九六二年冷战高峰期。

sentences.english: The traffic's bumper to bumper, it must be rush hour.
sentences.chinese: 车一辆接着一辆，现在肯定是交通高峰期。

sentences.english: Harvest, though, stands as the coming-of-age of the Baby Boomer generation.
sentences.chinese: 尽管《收获》将屹立于成年的“生育高峰期一代”。

sentences.english: HFMD activity peaked in June and has declined since then.
sentences.chinese: 手足口病的高峰期于六月出现，然后有下降趋势。

sentences.english: The peak of the outbreak occurred 3 weeks ago in Benguela and Bengo provinces.
sentences.chinese: 在本格拉和本戈省，疫情高峰期发生在3周之前。

sentences.english: The highest coefficient of mutual interference appeared during the ovipositing peak.
sentences.chinese: 在土蜂产卵高峰期，种内干扰系数最高。

sentences.english: Activity peaks this month, when ocean-surface waters are warmest.
sentences.chinese: 海洋表层水温度最高的月份是飓风活动的高峰期。

sentences.english: During the prime time of real estate market, they may also appear at the sales office of new housing development.
sentences.chinese: 在楼市高峰期，他们还会出现在新楼盘的售楼处。

sentences.english: The peak reproduction of sheathed bacteria was in the summer.
sentences.chinese: 夏季为鞘细菌繁殖高峰期。

sentences.english: "It is of concern because as we go into winter that is when we see our peak of flu," Rawlinson said.
sentences.chinese: 令人关切的原因是因为我们进入冬季流感高峰期。

sentences.english: In order to get out of the peak-hour traffic, we must start early.
sentences.chinese: 我们得早点儿动身以避开交通高峰期。

sentences.english: It's rush hour now; that road may be blocked .
sentences.chinese: 现在是交通高峰期，那条路可能堵着呢。
